    <section class="about__panel page-panel">
      <div class="about__content">
        <p class="about__intro"><strong>Zipply is a smart URL shortener and QR platform.</strong> It helps individuals and teams create short links, generate QR codes, and track performance in one clean dashboard.</p>

        <h2>1. What Zipply Does</h2>
        <p>Zipply allows you to create shortened URLs, generate QR codes, monitor click analytics, and manage link history from a single account. Every action is designed for speed and simplicity.</p>

        <h2>2. Plans That Match Real Usage</h2>
        <p>Zipply currently offers three plans:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Normal (Free):</strong> 3 short URLs + 2 QR codes per day</li>
          <li><strong>Pro:</strong> 10 short URLs + 10 QR codes per day</li>
          <li><strong>Plus:</strong> 25 short URLs + 25 QR codes per day</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Usage limits reset daily at midnight IST so tracking remains consistent for all users.</p>

        <h2>3. Built for Current Workflow</h2>
        <p>The platform includes email OTP verification, secure JWT authentication, click tracking, QR history, and dashboard-level usage visibility so users can understand performance without extra tools.</p>

        <h2>4. Tech Stack</h2>
        <p>Zipply is built with Node.js, Express, MongoDB, EJS, and Bootstrap, with Razorpay integration for plan upgrades.</p>

        <h2>5. Security & Privacy</h2>
        <p>Passwords are hashed, sessions are token-based, and user data is protected through secure backend validation and access control.</p>

        <h2>6. Mission</h2>
        <p>Our goal is to provide a reliable link and QR platform that stays easy for beginners but powerful enough for real production use.</p>

